- Use Testcontainers for isolated integration tests.
- Install Docker on your machine.
- Add Testcontainers dependency to your `pom.xml`:
  ```xml
  <dependency>
      <groupId>org.testcontainers</groupId>
      <artifactId>testcontainers</artifactId>
      <version>1.17.3</version>
      <scope>test</scope>
  </dependency>
  ```
- Configure Testcontainer in your test class:
  ```java
  @Testcontainers
  public class MyIntegrationTest {
      @Container
      private PostgreSQLContainer<?> postgreSQLContainer = new PostgreSQLContainer<>("postgres:15")
          .withDatabaseName("mydb")
          .withUsername("user")
          .withPassword("password");

      @Autowired
      private DataSource dataSource;

      @BeforeEach
      public void setUp() {
          // Initialize your test data here
      }
  }
  ```
- Use `@TestPropertySource` to override properties for testing:
  ```java
  @TestPropertySource(properties = "spring.datasource.url=jdbc:tc:postgresql:15:///mydb")
  ```
- Run tests with Maven:
  ```sh
  mvn test
  ```
- For embedded PostgreSQL, use `EmbeddedPostgres` from `com.opentable.db.postgresql` for unit tests.
